messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 6/4/2003 9:07:01 PM Eastern Daylight Time,
Unschooling-dotcom@yahoogroups.com writes:


> There are many times I just can't watch that type of movie.
> I don't fear ghosts, spirits, or demons, but I do have a big inner
> fear of the things real people can do.
>

Stephen King. I have NO problems with "Christine", "It", "Dreamcatcher"
---things like that. I read, but have NOT watched, "Misery". "Gerald's Game" could
be *too* real. Haven't watched "Cujo" either. "Silence of the Lambs"----brrrr.

Psychopaths, Sociopaths (My dad's a psychiatrist---I know many of
them!)---these people are REAL! I stay away from REAL scary. Fake scary's fun.


~Kelly
